# elizaos/elizaos.github.io Monthly Report (November 2025)

## üöÄ Highlights
Development in November focused on expanding the project's ecosystem integration. The primary activity involved a significant update to the pipeline configuration, incorporating twelve new active repositories. This expansion reflects a push to broaden the scope of monitored projects, including both core ElizaOS components and various community plugins.

## üõ†Ô∏è Key Developments
### Pipeline and Repository Integration
- The project's monitoring and development pipeline was updated to include 12 actively maintained repositories. This change, introduced in pull request [#169](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/169), brings more of the ElizaOS ecosystem into the central development workflow. The newly added repositories consist of 3 core components (`x402.elizaos.ai`, `spartan`, `jeju`) and 9 plugins (`chart`, `analytics`, `jupiter`, `trust`, `rolodex`, `birdeye`, `digitaltwin`, `mysql`, `elizaos-cl`).

## üêõ Issues & Triage
Based on the provided reports, there was no activity related to issues this month.
- **Closed Issues:** No issues were reported as closed.
- **New & Active Issues:** No new issues were opened, and there were no updates on existing active issues.

## üí¨ Community & Collaboration
The available data for November did not contain information regarding community discussions, new contributors, or collaborative activities on pull requests and issues.
